The article discusses the signing of a new law, H.R. 6256, by the President on December 23, 2021. The law bans imports from the Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region in China and imposes sanctions on foreign individuals who are responsible for forced labor in the region. The article also expresses gratitude to Speaker Pelosi, Leader Schumer, Representatives McGovern and Chris Smith, and Senators Merkley and Rubio for their leadership in relation to this issue.